	&lt;li&gt;This phrase encourages self-reliance and the idea that people shape their own lives based on their actions, choices, and abilities, which is exactly what Emma needs to understand.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the sentence would read like this:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;Emma should stop being jealous of her friend&amp;rsquo;s success and focus on her own capabilities. After all, every man is the architect of his own fortune.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

